@node "WHATIS" "WhAT Is It?"
À[ What Is It? ]À

Smart  Signature  has  a  double  function:   first  of all it improves the
internal  (and very ugly) default upload signature given to new users, then it
can be used as a sort of /X SENT command to change and center the upload
signature.

                                 User: John Doe

Old Default Signature:                                        -John Doe

dTC SmARt SiGnAtUre Installed: [-----------------------( John Doe )---]

See the difference and install it..

 ** THIS DOOR HAS BEEN CODED FOLLOWING THE OFFICIAL DAYDREAM DEVELOPER   ** 
 ** DOCUMENTATION AND IT'S ABLE TO HANDLE A LOSS OF CARRIER IN THE RIGHT ** 
 ** WAY, WITHOUT LOCKING THE SYSTEM AS OTHER DOORS DO..                  **
@endnode

@node "USAGE" "UsAgE"
À[ UsAGe ]À

After you have installed it,  SmArT SiGnATUre automatically sets the new users
default upload signature to its default.

When it's invoked as a door, it allows you to edit your upload signature (E),
center it (C), use the default one (D) and save it (S).
@endnode

@node "INSTALL" "InStAllATiON"
À[ InsTALLaTION ]À

First of all copy SmArTSig.X to your doors: directory..

If  you  want  Smart  Signature  to autmoatically change the default upload
signature  of new users, you must add to your EditUser.GFX and EditUser.TXT the
following line:

 Ddoors:SMsig.X %N NEW||

Ie:

This is the default EditUser.txt that comes with DayDream, with sM installed..

                           User Data For  R

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 1) Real Name............:  R
 2) Handle...............:  H
 3) Organization.........:  O
 4) Zip Code And City....:  Z
 5) Voice Phone Number...:  V
 6) PassWord.............:  A
 7) Screen Lenght........:  S
 8) Default Protocol.....:  T
 9) UpLoad Signature.....:  U
 0) Computer Model.......:  C

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 Ddoors:SMsig.X %N NEW||


Then, if you want to use Smart Siganture as a SENT door too,  add this to your
DAYDREAM.CFG ( supposing that you keep your doors in DOORS: )

 + 
 DOOR_COMMAND.. SENT
 DOOR_TYPE..... 1 
 DOOR_SECURITY. 10
 DOOR_EXECUTE.. DOORS:SmartSig.X %N 
 + 

rIGHT?
@endnode

